article_title: Oil Gains on U.S. Output Expectations, Weaker Dollar
article_text:
Oil prices rose for a fourth straight session Tuesday on fresh signs that U.S. oil production is nearing a peak.

Crude-oil production in North Dakota fell for the second straight month in February, the North Dakota Industrial Commission’s Department of Mineral Resources said Tuesday. Production averaged 1.18 million barrels a day in the month,...
